FBIS3-37655 "drsov035_a_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Kostikov Says Yeltsin Bolstered by Bosnia Initiative LD2102131194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1200 GMT 21 Feb 94 LD2102131194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Russian president's press secretary, Vyacheslav Kostikov, has said in an interview with INTERFAX that Boris Yeltsin's Bosnia initiative has lifted the danger from a crisis threatening to acquire worldwide dimensions and laid the foundations for a definitive settlement. Russia, the press secretary believes, has in fact won a vital battle for global status. This is important for the domestic political scene, in that it strengthens Boris Yeltsin's position.
